author: PAUL SCHWARTZ
title: H.S. girls track and field: Westwood's Jessia Molina Wake Forest bound - Girls Track
text:
Bergen County indoor shot put record holder and multiple State Meet of Champions medalist Jessica Molina of Westwood verbally committed to accept a track and field scholarship next fall at Wake Forest University on Monday.
Molina, who set the county record indoors (48 feet, 10 inches) last winter in winning the Eastern States championship and finished sixth in the nationals, chose Wake Forest over South Carolina, Miami and Penn State.
Molina, last season's North Jersey Indoor Field Athlete of the Year, placed in both the indoor and outdoor State Meet of Champions in the shot put last season, and has career outdoor bests of 46-9 in the shot (second all-time Bergen), 139-5 in the discus (third) and 122-9 in the javelin.
